messages.content:
{
    "thought_on_cooking_style": "The cooking style presented in the given recipes emphasizes freshness and simplicity, allowing the natural flavors of the seafood to shine through. The use of classic sauces and accompaniments such as horseradish and mignonette enhances the taste without overpowering the main ingredients. The New England clam chowder recipe showcases a traditional approach to creating a rich and comforting soup, with attention to building layers of flavor through the use of bacon, leeks, and spices.",
    "thought_on_recipe": "In keeping with the style of the given recipes, the recipe for clams and oysters with garlic bread will focus on the natural flavors of the seafood, complemented by the aromatic garlic bread. The recipe will involve simple yet precise techniques to prepare the seafood, ensuring they are clean and easy to eat, while the garlic bread will offer a crispy, flavorful contrast to the delicate texture of the clams and oysters.",
    "recipe":
        {
            "title": "Garlic Bread with Fresh Clams and Oysters",
            "description": "This recipe brings together the succulent taste of fresh clams and oysters with the aromatic crunch of homemade garlic bread. Served with a side of lemon wedges and optional dipping sauces, this dish is perfect as an appetizer or a light main course.",
            "list_of_steps": [
                {
                    "step": "Preheat your oven to 375F (190C) for the garlic bread. Meanwhile, place clams and oysters in the freezer for 10 to 15 minutes to make them easier to shuck."
                },
                {
                    "step": "For the garlic bread, mix together 1/2 cup of softened unsalted butter, 3 minced garlic cloves, 1 tablespoon of freshly chopped parsley, and a pinch of salt. Cut a baguette into 1/2-inch slices without cutting all the way through, and spread the garlic butter mixture between the slices."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Wrap the garlic bread in aluminum foil and bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. Then, uncover and bake for an additional 5 minutes or until the edges are golden and crispy."
                },
                {
                    "step": "While the bread is baking, start shucking the clams and oysters using the techniques described in the provided recipes, ensuring that they are clean and ready to be served."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Arrange the shucked clams and oysters on a serving platter with lemon wedges and optional sauces such as cocktail sauce, mignonette, or a simple vinaigrette."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Once the garlic bread is done, let it cool slightly before serving alongside the fresh clams and oysters."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Garnish the platter with additional chopped parsley or chives for color and serve immediately while the bread is warm and the seafood is chilled."
                }
            ]
        }
}
